Visited this establishment when I came to D.C. For my birthday. Went to the bar to buy a double shot of Vodka. She came back with "2 shots", gave her a fifty dollar bill and she brought me back $6. She started to walk off and I asked where the rest of my change was and she told me I asked for 2 double shots and they cost $22 each. I then reminded her that I asked for a double shot, not a quadruple shot. She took the shots back and returned with a one shot, shot glass; poured it half full and stated that's one shot. I said ok; she then filled the shot glass up and said that's 2 shots. Where I replied ok. She walks off and start serving other patrons. I asked the manager where she was with my change. He said she will give it to me. After not receiving my change I call her back over myself and requested my change. She still was trying to charge me for the shots she took away but wanted me to settle with their so called two shots and still charge me $44. Needless to say I got my $22. If they want to charge $22 for a double shot that's in actuality one then that's fine. Just give me what I asked for and don't play with my money. The overall atmosphere was great but I will never spend another dime there.
